WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:07.560
This programme contains
strong language 

00:19.240 --> 00:22.360
FOOTBALL CROWD ROARS

00:25.960 --> 00:29.200
MUSIC PLAYING

01:01.560 --> 01:03.040
FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING

01:03.040 --> 01:05.120
Oh, Jesus Christ!
Sorry, Ref.

01:05.120 --> 01:06.280
The door was open.

01:06.280 --> 01:07.760
What can I do for you, Mitch?

01:07.760 --> 01:09.520
Well, I'm just checking with
you

01:09.520 --> 01:11.400
if it's OK for me to be
pitch-side during the match.

01:11.400 --> 01:13.200
You know, get the crowd
going and everything.

01:13.200 --> 01:14.520
Not during the game, no.

01:14.520 --> 01:17.000
Pre-match, half-time only.
Oh.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.280
It's just that Rovers have brought
Scotty the Shrimp.

01:19.280 --> 01:21.440
I thought we could get a bit
of play-fighting going, you know?

01:21.440 --> 01:24.360
In jest, like, have a laugh.
No, I can't allow it. I'm sorry.

01:24.360 --> 01:25.680
I'm not having the players
distracted by

01:25.680 --> 01:28.160
a six-foot prawn knocking
seven shades of shite
out of a...

01:28.160 --> 01:30.280
..whatever it is you are.

01:30.280 --> 01:31.920
This is not America, Mitch.

01:31.920 --> 01:33.240
I understand.

01:33.240 --> 01:35.880
Hey, it's your last-ever game
today, isn't it?

01:35.880 --> 01:37.160
It is, yes.

01:37.160 --> 01:39.840
Well, I just want to say it's been
an absolute privilege to work
with you.

01:39.840 --> 01:40.920
Fantastic.

01:40.920 --> 01:43.800
And may the best team win.

01:43.800 --> 01:45.320
Indeed.

01:48.160 --> 01:50.560
TOILET FLUSHES

01:53.680 --> 01:55.720
I'd give it a minute
before you go in there.

01:55.720 --> 01:57.440
A few, er, pre-match nerves.

01:57.440 --> 01:59.440
Well, it's a big game, isn't it?

01:59.440 --> 02:02.520
It is. When I worked
at the San Siro,

02:02.520 --> 02:05.080
the WC was adjacent to the
showers with a separate door,

02:05.080 --> 02:07.160
and it had a self-lowering
lavatory seat.

02:07.160 --> 02:08.440
You felt pampered.

02:08.440 --> 02:10.880
You're really early. What time
is it?

02:10.880 --> 02:12.920
1:58:59.

02:12.920 --> 02:15.840
I like to be fully uniformed
before the captains' meeting.

02:15.840 --> 02:17.760
Gives me that extra degree of
authority.

02:17.760 --> 02:20.400
Oh, most definitely. I've known some
refs slumming round

02:20.400 --> 02:22.200
in sweat pants with a beer
in their hand

02:22.200 --> 02:24.240
at 20 to three like they're at
a family barbecue.

02:24.240 --> 02:27.920
No, you're one of the pros, Martin.
A role model. I've always said it.

02:27.920 --> 02:29.760
That's why you've lasted
as long as you have.

02:29.760 --> 02:31.120
Thank you, Brendan,
I appreciate that.

02:31.120 --> 02:33.440
Was that Mitch I could hear
just now? It was.

02:33.440 --> 02:35.200
I've never seen him out of that
costume.

02:35.200 --> 02:36.920
Do you think he could be
a St Bernard?

02:36.920 --> 02:39.120
Well, I was thinking more chipmunk,
but you might be right.

02:39.120 --> 02:42.760
They have got the shittest
gym here I have ever seen.

02:42.760 --> 02:44.960
My ex-wife's got a better
treadmill in her utility room.

02:44.960 --> 02:46.680
Well, admittedly
the facilities are a little tired,

02:46.680 --> 02:50.000
but if United win promotion today,
that's all gonna change.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.600
That's a big if.
At the San Siro,

02:51.600 --> 02:54.440
they had a treadmill in the
officials' changing room,
and someone came round

02:54.440 --> 02:57.400
every 20 minutes and replenished
the towels. It's the little touches.

02:57.400 --> 02:58.680
Where's Oggy?

02:58.680 --> 03:00.240
Where'd you expect him to
be?

03:00.240 --> 03:01.760
Stuffing his face at the
vending machine.

03:01.760 --> 03:03.120
SIGHS

03:03.120 --> 03:04.720
We only had lunch two hours ago.

03:04.720 --> 03:06.760
I mean, the captains'll be here
any minute.

03:06.760 --> 03:08.880
We've got to synchronise our
watches, go through the team
sheet...

03:08.880 --> 03:10.520
Shitting Nora!

03:10.520 --> 03:12.320
Oh, sorry, Phil.

03:12.320 --> 03:13.920
That was me. There's no Glade.

03:13.920 --> 03:16.680
Did a rat crawl up your arse
and die?! Pre-match nerves.

03:16.680 --> 03:18.040
You're the fourth official.

03:18.040 --> 03:20.840
What have you got to be nervous
about? Holding up the wrong numbers
on the board?

03:20.840 --> 03:22.600
Yeah, you may joke,
but that has happened.

03:22.600 --> 03:25.360
Barry Crop once accidentally
signalled for 56 minutes'

03:25.360 --> 03:28.440
added time at a Sheffield derby
game. And it was on Sky.

03:28.440 --> 03:30.600
Took him a good few months
to live that down, I tell you.

03:30.600 --> 03:32.680
At the San Siro...  All right,
Brendan, give it a rest,

03:32.680 --> 03:34.280
for fuck's sake!

03:36.880 --> 03:38.400
Sorry.

03:39.480 --> 03:43.000
I'll just, er, go and squirt a few
drops of Aramis in the pan.

03:43.000 --> 03:46.160
See if it'll help, er,
dissimilate the odour.

03:51.080 --> 03:52.480
DOOR CLOSES

03:53.840 --> 03:55.840
You shouldn't speak to
Brendan like that.

03:55.840 --> 03:58.400
I heard he's being considered
for the select group next
season,

03:58.400 --> 03:59.760
so you could be working under him.

03:59.760 --> 04:02.760
Is that how you see the assistants?
Under the referee?

04:02.760 --> 04:04.960
I thought we were a team?
We are a team,

04:04.960 --> 04:07.480
and that includes the fourth
official.

04:07.480 --> 04:10.320
If we don't respect ourselves,
how are we gonna get respect
from the players?

04:10.320 --> 04:12.480
He's so boring, though,
Martin!

04:12.480 --> 04:13.760
He is boring, yes.

04:13.760 --> 04:15.840
And that's a very good quality
in a referee.

04:15.840 --> 04:18.160
He's anonymously
competent, and that...

04:18.160 --> 04:20.240
..takes guts.
Brendan hasn't got any guts.

04:20.240 --> 04:21.840
He's dropped them all in there!

04:23.280 --> 04:26.760
Right, well, I think that's, er,
taken the edge off it.

04:28.760 --> 04:31.600
Anyway, if anyone should be
nervous, it's me.

04:31.600 --> 04:34.520
Just seen Howard arrive
with half a dozen Qataris.

04:34.520 --> 04:37.160
They've come to cast their
eye over me for 2022.

04:37.160 --> 04:39.840
Oh, you don't think it's because
it's one of the biggest games
in English football?

04:39.840 --> 04:41.360
Well, yeah, there is that.

04:41.360 --> 04:43.000
But if it goes well for me today,

04:43.000 --> 04:46.280
I could be running the line
at a World Cup, Martin.

04:46.280 --> 04:48.760
Imagine being able to flag
Neymar offside.

04:48.760 --> 04:50.760
We are not the story, Phil.

04:50.760 --> 04:53.400
We are neutral officiators.
Never forget that.

04:53.400 --> 04:56.760
Yeah, whatever. If I'm not back in
20 minutes, phone for the fire
brigade.

04:59.360 --> 05:00.640
Ugh!

05:02.160 --> 05:03.680
He has got a lot to learn,
that one.

05:07.360 --> 05:09.040
Are those City pants, Brendan?

05:09.040 --> 05:10.200
No!

05:10.200 --> 05:11.600
Clean on this morning.

05:12.560 --> 05:15.400
Oh, City. Yes, well we're away
at Preston today.

05:15.400 --> 05:17.360
Should be good for a point at
least, don't you think?

05:17.360 --> 05:18.640
Consolidate a play-off place.

05:18.640 --> 05:20.680
You know my thoughts about team
colours in the changing room.

05:20.680 --> 05:23.320
Yes, but it's the last day of the
season. What with us
being City fans...?

05:23.320 --> 05:24.920
Take them off, please.

05:24.920 --> 05:26.440
Of course.

05:26.440 --> 05:27.880
Sorry, Martin.

05:32.080 --> 05:34.200
It's been a good season for
us, but, er...

05:35.280 --> 05:37.800
..without the investment, you know,
you can't really compete.

05:38.800 --> 05:41.800
Still, if we win today,
we might finish third.

05:41.800 --> 05:44.920
We've always been the
bridesmaid, never the bride.

05:44.920 --> 05:46.360
True.

05:46.360 --> 05:48.800
Without that cash we'll never be up
there playing with the big boys.

05:48.800 --> 05:51.880
Oh, if I had a pound for every time
I'd heard you say that, Brendan.

05:51.880 --> 05:53.840
You all right, boss?
How you feeling?

05:53.840 --> 05:56.080
Hey, it's filling up
out there, you know.

05:56.080 --> 05:58.280
You can cut the atmosphere
with a cake slice.

05:58.280 --> 05:59.320
Sorry.

05:59.320 --> 06:01.080
Have you warmed up, Oggy? Yeah.

06:01.080 --> 06:03.800
I did hot yoga in the bath
this morning. I am serious.

06:03.800 --> 06:05.520
Don't worry, boss.

06:05.520 --> 06:06.640
I'll do me stretches.

06:06.640 --> 06:08.080
Where's Phil, anyway?

06:08.080 --> 06:10.120
Doesn't he normally lead
the ref-aerobics around now?

06:10.120 --> 06:12.240
He's shaving.
Yeah, I bet he is.

06:12.240 --> 06:13.320
Bloody Sky's here.

06:13.320 --> 06:15.640
He'll be doing a back, sack
and crack wax, knowing him.

06:15.640 --> 06:18.680
Hey, 20 quid he gels all his
hair up like Gareth Gates.

06:18.680 --> 06:22.040
No betting, Oggy!
You've been warned before.

06:22.040 --> 06:24.320
Only joking! Christ, Martin!

06:24.320 --> 06:26.080
Well, it's not a joking matter,
is it?

06:26.080 --> 06:29.720
What's up with you? This is meant
to be your retirement.

06:29.720 --> 06:30.960
Biggest game of your career.

06:30.960 --> 06:33.000
You should be relishing it.
I am relishing it.

06:33.000 --> 06:35.320
Well, tell your face. It's longer
than one of Brendan's stories.

06:35.320 --> 06:37.080
No offence.
None taken.

06:37.080 --> 06:39.400
We don't all enjoy ourselves
in the same way, Oggy.

06:39.400 --> 06:40.480
All right.

06:41.440 --> 06:44.520
So, goalie for United,
number 1, Charlie Evans.

06:44.520 --> 06:46.080
That's nice and easy.

06:46.080 --> 06:49.120
Back four - Ripley, Price,
Clyne and Cox.

06:49.120 --> 06:51.640
They're your solicitors,
aren't they, Brendan?

06:52.720 --> 06:55.520
Er, midfield is that Polish one
whose name I can never pronounce.

06:55.520 --> 06:57.560
Dzierzanowska.
That's him.

06:57.560 --> 06:59.320
Looks like two bad hands
at Scrabble.

06:59.320 --> 07:01.600
And up front, Calvin Cooke!

07:01.600 --> 07:03.120
I hope you've got his number,
boss.

07:04.760 --> 07:05.800
How d'you mean?

07:06.800 --> 07:08.040
Well, he's got a temper on
him.

07:08.040 --> 07:10.600
A lot of inner demons,
from what I've heard.

07:11.720 --> 07:14.320
Well, he'll be here in a
minute, so you can find out

07:14.320 --> 07:15.800
for yourself, can't you?

07:15.800 --> 07:17.440
Right, can we synchronise
watches, please?

07:17.440 --> 07:18.720
Oh, we don't have to do that.

07:18.720 --> 07:20.320
It's not Mission: Impossible.

07:20.320 --> 07:24.240
I've got 14:02 and 52 seconds.

07:24.240 --> 07:26.120
Er, six minutes past two...

07:26.120 --> 07:29.720
And let's synchronise, please.
56 seconds, 57...

07:29.720 --> 07:31.320
BEEPING
Hang on, hang on.

07:31.320 --> 07:32.920
I can only put this one
forwards, it won't go back.

07:32.920 --> 07:35.760
Oh, for God's sake!
It's three o'clock kick-off,

07:35.760 --> 07:37.360
quarter to four for a pie
and a piss,

07:37.360 --> 07:39.560
ten to five, final score
and get first round in.

07:39.560 --> 07:40.600
It's not rocket science.

07:40.600 --> 07:43.920
Fuckin' lukewarm water and
the shampoo's like dog spunk.

07:43.920 --> 07:45.480
Why hasn't this club
got any money?

07:45.480 --> 07:47.280
Hey! They're like a old bra -

07:47.280 --> 07:49.640
no cups and crap support.
I thank you!

07:49.640 --> 07:51.800
They had Aveda products
throughout at the San Siro.

07:51.800 --> 07:53.400
It's like a boutique hotel.

07:53.400 --> 07:56.360
Do we know if Sky are showing
this in 4K or just in HD?

07:56.360 --> 07:58.240
I don't know. can we just...
Ah, there you go!

07:58.240 --> 07:59.720
What did I tell you? 20 quid.

07:59.720 --> 08:01.840
Worried about your bald spot,
Phil? Fuck off, Oggy!

08:01.840 --> 08:03.320
ANGRILY: Can we
synchronise watches, please?

08:03.320 --> 08:04.920
Hey, I saw you on the
treadmill earlier

08:04.920 --> 08:06.600
practising your backwards
running.

08:06.600 --> 08:09.200
Bullshit.
It's true!

08:09.200 --> 08:12.120
He practises running backwards doing
his Collina face so he can get

08:12.120 --> 08:13.360
a nice big close-up on TV.

08:13.360 --> 08:15.440
No, it's so I can get better
peripheral vision.

08:15.440 --> 08:18.360
It's better than you chugging up and
down like Mr fuckin' Creosote.

08:18.360 --> 08:20.640
Oh, is that right? Mr
Creosote? Guys, please!

08:23.280 --> 08:27.920
If United win today, they get
automatic promotion
to the Premier League.

08:27.920 --> 08:30.520
With merit payments and TV
rights, that's a huge windfall.

08:30.520 --> 08:32.960
150 million, according to
The Mirror. Exactly.

08:32.960 --> 08:34.320
And if Rovers win, they avoid

08:34.320 --> 08:37.120
relegation into the lower leagues
and financial oblivion.

08:37.120 --> 08:41.000
So it's up to us to work as a
team to ensure a fair result.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.200
You know, it's going to be
tense enough out there

08:43.200 --> 08:45.680
without you two glaring at
each other across the pitch

08:45.680 --> 08:47.360
like Bette Davis and Joan
Crawford.

08:48.440 --> 08:49.480
He started it.

08:49.480 --> 08:51.280
MOCKINGLY: "He started
it." I don't care!

08:52.480 --> 08:56.800
We have to be beyond reproach
in every decision we make.

08:58.040 --> 09:00.360
So show some professionalism.
KNOCK ON DOOR

09:02.080 --> 09:03.320
Ah, Calvin, come in.

09:03.320 --> 09:04.920
Is Nico with you?

09:04.920 --> 09:06.560
Haven't seen him. Ah, Oggy,
go and get Nico, will you?

09:06.560 --> 09:09.960
Tell him he's already three
minutes late for
the captains' meeting.

09:09.960 --> 09:13.760
And you, go and do your
manscaping, or whatever it is
you do in there.

09:14.880 --> 09:16.800
You, check the match ball.

09:16.800 --> 09:19.000
I want it 12.5 psi.

09:19.000 --> 09:20.160
Yes, Ref. Sorry.

09:24.120 --> 09:25.200
What's this?

09:25.200 --> 09:26.440
Retirement card.

09:26.440 --> 09:28.120
What, from you
or the whole team?

09:28.120 --> 09:29.320
What do you think?

09:29.320 --> 09:31.680
Hardly going to be walking around
with my own card for you, am I?

09:31.680 --> 09:33.160
So, big game.

09:33.160 --> 09:34.280
Yeah. Yeah.

09:34.280 --> 09:35.680
How you feeling?

09:35.680 --> 09:36.960
I'm OK.

09:36.960 --> 09:38.040
Can I kiss you?

09:42.760 --> 09:45.240
What happened to your rules?

09:45.240 --> 09:46.920
Please.

09:46.920 --> 09:49.400
It's a big game for me as well,
you know.

10:01.840 --> 10:04.040
So now...
..you've just gotta give us

10:04.040 --> 10:05.760
a couple of penalties, right?
CHUCKLES

10:05.760 --> 10:07.440
I'd love it if I could. But I can't.

10:07.440 --> 10:09.920
Not even if there's tugging in
the box? Don't even joke about it.

10:09.920 --> 10:12.960
If the PGMOL ever found out...
You're retiring!

10:12.960 --> 10:14.360
Yeah, but it's my reputation,
isn't it?

10:14.360 --> 10:16.080
Not to mention the legal
consequences.

10:16.080 --> 10:17.840
I mean not just for me,
but for the club!

10:17.840 --> 10:19.920
Martin, nobody's gonna find out.

10:19.920 --> 10:21.200
Relax.

10:22.600 --> 10:24.120
Eh? I've got your back.

10:27.560 --> 10:28.840
I love you.

10:30.480 --> 10:31.760
DOOR OPENS

10:31.760 --> 10:34.560
Ah, Nico, nice of you
to join us.

10:34.560 --> 10:36.920
Right, now, I want a good
clean game

10:36.920 --> 10:39.280
with plenty of flow and all the
focus on the football.

10:39.280 --> 10:41.960
Everybody on that pitch
knows the laws of the game.

10:41.960 --> 10:44.600
And if we stick to that, there's no
reason we can't have a fitting,

10:44.600 --> 10:47.080
dignified, trouble-free end
to the season.

10:47.080 --> 10:48.960
Understand?
WHISTLE BLOWS

10:56.840 --> 10:58.520
WHISTLE BLOWS

10:59.760 --> 11:02.400
CROWD: The referee's a wanker!
The referee's a wanker!

11:02.400 --> 11:04.240
OGGY: Get him under
control, you flaming animal!

11:04.240 --> 11:05.640
Oggy!
He chucked a bap at me!

11:05.640 --> 11:07.720
A what?
A bap! A bacon bap!

11:07.720 --> 11:09.800
Who did? That Polish one.
Dirty bastard.

11:09.800 --> 11:11.520
Dzierzanowska?
Yeah, that's him.

11:11.520 --> 11:13.600
Flaming animal! I want his
name in the book.

11:13.600 --> 11:15.440
If you can frigging spell it..
You're bleeding.

11:15.440 --> 11:17.360
Eh? No, it's just ketchup.

11:17.360 --> 11:19.040
Ah... What should I put
in the report, Martin?

11:19.040 --> 11:22.160
Just put, "Food thrown in tunnel."
We'll see what the damage is later.

11:22.160 --> 11:25.280
At the San Siro, the ushers
escorted you all the way
down the tunnel.

11:25.280 --> 11:26.800
And we had our own
espresso machine.

11:26.800 --> 11:29.280
This was before they became
commonplace. They're more
ubiquitous than kettles now.

11:29.280 --> 11:31.200
Where's Phil?
Oh, he got collared by Mitch.

11:31.200 --> 11:33.040
He was trying to show him
video replay on his phone.

11:33.040 --> 11:35.120
Well, he shouldn't be
looking at that! I know,

11:35.120 --> 11:36.600
but Phil is a pro. I'm sure he can
handle himself.

11:36.600 --> 11:38.760
Did you notice how he went
and picked up the match ball

11:38.760 --> 11:40.160
soon as you blew the whistle?

11:40.160 --> 11:41.560
The he just stood there
with his chin up

11:41.560 --> 11:43.160
waiting for the Steadicam guy
to circle round him?

11:43.160 --> 11:44.680
Oggy's right. That's not
protocol.

11:44.680 --> 11:46.600
He wears eyeliner, you know.
No, he doesn't.

11:46.600 --> 11:48.000
Yes, he does!

11:48.000 --> 11:49.120
Did you not see him when
they had

11:49.120 --> 11:50.960
that minute's silence
for Butch Wilkins last year?

11:50.960 --> 11:52.640
It was running all down
his face!

11:52.640 --> 11:54.320
Linesman Minnelli, they
called him.

11:56.840 --> 11:58.240
It was a goal, wasn't it?

11:58.240 --> 11:59.360
It was a clear goal.

11:59.360 --> 12:01.400
There wasn't a hint of offside?
Not a chance.

12:01.400 --> 12:03.800
I think what they were
contesting was the throw-in.

12:03.800 --> 12:06.080
Don't look at me.
I was six foot away.

12:06.080 --> 12:08.600
That was a throw-in all day,
every day.

12:08.600 --> 12:10.720
Did you see it?
No, I was on the far side.

12:10.720 --> 12:12.840
And you're sure
it was a throw-in?

12:12.840 --> 12:15.200
May God strike me down.

12:15.200 --> 12:17.000
It was 18 inches off the line.

12:17.000 --> 12:18.640
What, in or out?
In!

12:18.640 --> 12:20.360
I've just seen the replay.
Shit!

12:20.360 --> 12:23.000
Nah, that's impossible. I saw it
cross with my own eyes.

12:23.000 --> 12:24.520
You should have gone to
Specsavers, then,
shouldn't you?

12:24.520 --> 12:25.680
Calvin wanted to talk to you

12:25.680 --> 12:27.080
but I told him he'd have to
wait until after the game.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.480
Yeah, well, quite right. It's only
half-time, for goodness' sake.

12:29.480 --> 12:30.560
Anything could happen yet!

12:30.560 --> 12:32.600
What did he say?
He's fuming!

12:32.600 --> 12:36.200
Mitch the fuckin' Meerkat
keeps on showing everyone
the footage on his phone.

12:36.200 --> 12:37.800
What do you mean, meerkat?
He's an otter!

12:37.800 --> 12:39.520
How can he be an otter?!

12:39.520 --> 12:41.080
Otters are mustelids with tiny
ears.

12:41.080 --> 12:42.760
All right, David
fucking Attenborough!

12:42.760 --> 12:45.200
