20:59.520 --> 21:02.720
a personal relationship between
a key player for United

21:02.720 --> 21:04.840
and the referee
Martin Rutherford.

21:04.840 --> 21:07.720
The trouble started, well,
it started in the first half

21:07.720 --> 21:09.840
with that controversial goal
for Rovers

21:09.840 --> 21:13.400
and the mysterious dismissal
at half-time of the United
captain Calvin Cooke,

21:13.400 --> 21:16.280
but it was compounded by an
extraordinary second half

21:16.280 --> 21:19.600
which saw Rutherford award a frankly
ludicrous penalty to United,

21:19.600 --> 21:22.000
which was missed,
and ordered to be retaken,

21:22.000 --> 21:25.000
not once, not twice,
but three times

21:25.000 --> 21:26.800
until Kirby scored to level
the game.

21:26.800 --> 21:29.960
This led to a mass brawl on
the pitch, five red cards...

21:32.240 --> 21:35.080
The press are going to have
an absolute field day with this.

21:35.080 --> 21:37.400
Are you kidding?
They already are.

21:37.400 --> 21:40.360
Robbie Savage has just been
on, tearing us to shreds.

21:40.360 --> 21:43.600
He even had a go at my hair, which
is the pot calling the kettle black.

21:44.760 --> 21:46.280
How's Martin?

21:46.280 --> 21:48.080
He's shaken but philosophical.

21:48.080 --> 21:50.560
I think he's aware his legacy
is somewhat tarnished.

21:50.560 --> 21:54.920
Somewhat? He's the Lance
Armstrong of football referees.

21:54.920 --> 21:56.240
He's fucked himself.

21:56.240 --> 21:58.240
Not...anatomically.

21:58.240 --> 22:00.920
Or professionally, as long
as we all stick together.

22:00.920 --> 22:03.560
He can't be blamed for them
players fighting like that.

22:03.560 --> 22:06.840
Brendan, he gave a penalty
for a handball

22:06.840 --> 22:08.040
against the goalkeeper!

22:08.040 --> 22:10.720
Well, he didn't know it
was the keeper, did he?

22:10.720 --> 22:13.120
What, the one in the big
bright red shirt with gloves on

22:13.120 --> 22:15.000
leaping through the air like
Superman?

22:15.000 --> 22:17.000
I think even Arsene Wenger
might have spotted that one.

22:17.000 --> 22:19.040
He was trying to even things
up.

22:19.040 --> 22:20.480
Just cancel out Oggy's mistake.

22:20.480 --> 22:22.280
We are going to stand by him,
aren't we?

22:22.280 --> 22:23.960
Well...like I say.

22:25.080 --> 22:26.600
He's fucked himself.

22:31.800 --> 22:33.480
They want to speak to you
next, Phil.

22:35.240 --> 22:37.200
Is Howard there?
Yeah.

22:37.200 --> 22:38.960
And the police.

22:40.640 --> 22:42.400
It's a criminal matter now,
apparently.

22:43.680 --> 22:45.120
Christ.

22:46.680 --> 22:48.600
Are the Qataris still here?

22:48.600 --> 22:51.000
You mean the Arabs?
I didn't see any.

22:51.000 --> 22:52.560
Fuck's sake!

22:53.920 --> 22:56.000
If this costs me my World Cup
spot...

22:57.080 --> 22:59.080
I've always liked you, Phil.

22:59.080 --> 23:00.440
You know that, don't you?

23:01.520 --> 23:04.120
Not in a Martin and Calvin
kind of way,

23:04.120 --> 23:06.080
more like professional....

23:06.080 --> 23:08.120
..respect.

23:08.120 --> 23:10.280
You won't dob me in it,
will you?

23:11.560 --> 23:13.320
Please.

23:21.720 --> 23:23.600
He's going to tell them
everything, isn't he?

23:23.600 --> 23:25.160
Course he is.

23:25.160 --> 23:28.400
He'll sing like a canary on The X
Factor to save his own skin.

23:28.400 --> 23:30.880
You'd better get yourself
a solicitor, pal.

23:32.040 --> 23:35.320
Whatever happened to
"What happens in the ref's
room stays in the ref's room"?

23:35.320 --> 23:36.800
Nah, different game now.

23:36.800 --> 23:38.880
You know when the rot set in?

23:38.880 --> 23:41.600
When they started putting
us in coloured jerseys.

23:41.600 --> 23:42.720
Ugh!

23:42.720 --> 23:45.000
Back in the day
you were the Man in Black.

23:45.000 --> 23:48.520
Big characters like George
Courtney. Keith Hackett.

23:48.520 --> 23:50.200
Yes. Men to be feared.

23:50.200 --> 23:54.240
Then the television money came in
and they demanded more colour.

23:54.240 --> 23:56.480
Pinks, greens, burgundies.

23:56.480 --> 24:00.440
We look more like Showaddywaddy
than football referees.

24:00.440 --> 24:02.680
Sports entertainment.

24:02.680 --> 24:05.480
No, it's all about the money
now.

24:05.480 --> 24:07.280
As you well know, Oggy.

24:07.280 --> 24:10.000
And that 15 grand won't take
you very far through the courts.

24:11.280 --> 24:14.680
I don't even think it was
an eastern betting syndicate.

24:14.680 --> 24:17.600
I think it was just one man
putting a voice on.

24:18.840 --> 24:22.840
Now I think of it, he
sounded more like Benny Hill
doing Mr Chow Mein.

24:24.280 --> 24:26.960
All right, boss? How's your
eye? Looks painful.

24:26.960 --> 24:28.280
Yeah, stings a bit, you know.

24:29.880 --> 24:31.400
Where's Phil?

24:31.400 --> 24:34.120
Oh, he's... He's giving his
statement to...

24:34.120 --> 24:36.000
..to Howard and the police.

24:37.520 --> 24:39.680
Well, bang goes my pension,
then, eh?

24:39.680 --> 24:41.480
I don't think they can, er,

24:41.480 --> 24:44.160
hold you entirely responsible,
Martin.

24:44.160 --> 24:45.920
You did it in the spirit
of fairness.

24:45.920 --> 24:47.320
No, I did it...

24:48.920 --> 24:50.120
I did it for love.

24:52.840 --> 24:54.200
Has Calvin been around?

24:54.200 --> 24:56.640
No. I believe his agent
whisked him away.

24:56.640 --> 24:58.240
He'll be wanting to get his
side of the story

24:58.240 --> 25:00.800
in the Sunday papers
before all the rumours start.

25:00.800 --> 25:02.080
Yeah, of course...

25:03.240 --> 25:04.280
He's a good lad.

25:07.640 --> 25:11.080
If there's any way of keeping
my name out of it,
I'd appreciate it, boss.

25:11.080 --> 25:12.520
Oh, yeah, of course.

25:12.520 --> 25:14.480
Well, I'll do what I can.

25:16.160 --> 25:17.400
Thanks.

25:19.800 --> 25:21.720
Hey, er, give my love
to the San Siro.

25:21.720 --> 25:23.000
Heh!

25:23.000 --> 25:25.600
In bocca al lupo.
CHUCKLES

25:25.600 --> 25:26.920
Good luck.

25:59.600 --> 26:01.160
KNOCK AT DOOR

